Collection Collection protocols  To implement a protocol, objects must support certain operations. Most collections implement container, sized and iterable. All except dict and set are sequences Container: membership testing using in and not in Sized: Determine number of elements with len(s) Iterable: Can produce an iterator with iter(s), e.g.
 for item in iterable: do_something(item) `len(s)`  Sequence:
 Retrieve elements by index, e.g. item = seq[index] Find items by value index = seq.
